// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/Driver/emit_verilog/single_module.test — M7 US1 keystone
// fixture (T020). Asserts that `nslc -emit=verilog` on a minimal
// single-module source produces a syntactically valid Verilog
// `module` body with the expected register + assign shape.
//
// Per `spec.md` § User Story 1 acceptance scenario #1 +
// `driver-emit-verilog.contract.md` §7.
//
// **State at authoring (TDD; Constitution Principle VIII)**: RED.
// At the time this fixture lands, `Compilation::runCIRCTPasses` +
// `emitVerilog` bodies are wired and exporting via
// `circt::exportVerilog`; the precise output shape (Verilog
// statement formatting, signal-name escaping) is what
// `circt::exportVerilog` emits and is *outside our control*. The
// CHECK lines pin properties the pipeline must satisfy:
//   - the module declaration appears with the input source's name
//   - at least one always_ff block emits for the reg `r`
//   - the output `q` gets a continuous assign

// RUN: %nslc -emit=verilog %S/fixtures/single_module.nsl | %FileCheck %s

// Verilog `module` declaration with our top name.
// CHECK-LABEL: module M

// Active-HIGH async reset on `r` per M6 Q2 → C convention
// (the implicit `m_clock` + `p_reset` ports per nsl_lang.ebnf §15
// lines 818, 820). Note: CIRCT's ExportVerilog emits SystemVerilog-
// 2005-style `always` blocks (not the SV-strict `always_ff`); both
// are accepted by iverilog -g2012 and verilator.
// CHECK: always @(posedge m_clock or posedge p_reset)

// Output `q` continuous-assigned from `r`.
// CHECK: assign q

// No `nsl.` / `fsm.` / `seq.` op residue — the M7 stock-CIRCT pass
// pipeline lowered them out. (`sv.` is permitted: ExportVerilog
// consumes it.)
// CHECK-NOT: nsl.
// CHECK-NOT: fsm.
// CHECK-NOT: seq.
